article.headline: Alcorn State 58, Jackson State 56
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Delvin Thompson scored 18 points and Alcorn State took over down the stretch in a 58-56 victory over Jackson State on Saturday night, the Braves' third straight win. Alcorn State (3-9, 3-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference) rallied from a big halftime deficit and overcame a huge game from the Tigers' Trey Johnson, the league's second-leading scorer who finished with 26 points. Jackson State led 27-15 at halftime before Alcorn State outscored the Tigers 43-29 in the second half. The Braves scored the final eight points of the game and held Jackson State to one point in the final 3 minutes. Alcorn State took the lead for good on a free throw by Clif Douglass with 1:11 to play. Jackson State had one last chance to win, but Charlie White missed a jumper. Douglass got the rebound, was fouled and made one free throw to close the scoring. Almaad Jackson finished with 15 points while Juan Wyatt had 10 points and 13 rebounds. Jackson State (6-9, 2-1) had its two-game winning streak snapped.
